import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['duration'] = pd.to_datetime(data['duration'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.hour
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['duration'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['duration'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['duration'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['duration'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['duration'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Duration (hours)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay_time'] = data['arr_delay'] - data['dep_delay']
    avg_delay_time_by_airline = data.groupby('carrier')['delay_time'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_delay_time_by_airline.index, avg_delay_time_by_airline.values, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(avg_delay_time_by_airline.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average delay time: {avg_delay_time_by_airline.mean():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Airline')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average delay time (minutes)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average delay time for flights?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['DEPARTURE_DELAY'] = pd.to_datetime(data['DEPARTURE_DELAY'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.time
    data['ARRIVAL_DELAY'] = pd.to_datetime(data['ARRIVAL_DELAY'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.time
    plt.scatter(data['DEPARTURE_DELAY'], data['ARRIVAL_DELAY'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Departure Delay')
    plt.ylabel('Arrival Delay')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between departure delay and arrival delay?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = data['distance'].astype(float)
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['CancellationCode'] = data['CancellationCode'].fillna('Not Cancelled')
    cancellation_reasons = data['CancellationCode'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(cancellation_reasons.index, cancellation_reasons.values)
    ax.set_title('What is the most common reason for flight cancellations?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Cancellation Reason')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
